CC   -!- FUNCTION: Catalyzes the condensation of acetyl-CoA with acetoacetyl-CoA
CC       to form 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-CoA (HMG-CoA). Functions in the
CC       mevalonate (MVA) pathway leading to isopentenyl diphosphate (IPP), a
CC       key precursor for the biosynthesis of isoprenoid compounds that are
CC       building blocks of archaeal membrane lipids. {ECO:0000256|HAMAP-
CC       Rule:MF_01409}.
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY:
CC       Reaction=acetoacetyl-CoA + acetyl-CoA + H2O = (3S)-3-hydroxy-3-
CC         methylglutaryl-CoA + CoA + H(+); Xref=Rhea:RHEA:10188,
CC         ChEBI:CHEBI:15377, ChEBI:CHEBI:15378, ChEBI:CHEBI:43074,
CC         ChEBI:CHEBI:57286, ChEBI:CHEBI:57287, ChEBI:CHEBI:57288; EC=2.3.3.10;
CC         Evidence={ECO:0000256|HAMAP-Rule:MF_01409};
CC   -!- PATHWAY: Metabolic intermediate biosynthesis; (R)-mevalonate
CC       biosynthesis; (R)-mevalonate from acetyl-CoA: step 2/3.
CC       {ECO:0000256|HAMAP-Rule:MF_01409}.
CC   -!- SUBUNIT: Interacts with acetoacetyl-CoA thiolase that catalyzes the
CC       precedent step in the pathway and with a DUF35 protein. The
CC       acetoacetyl-CoA thiolase/HMG-CoA synthase complex channels the
CC       intermediate via a fused CoA-binding site, which allows for efficient
CC       coupling of the endergonic thiolase reaction with the exergonic HMGCS
CC       reaction. {ECO:0000256|HAMAP-Rule:MF_01409}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the thiolase-like superfamily. Archaeal HMG-CoA
CC       synthase family. {ECO:0000256|HAMAP-Rule:MF_01409}.
CC   -!- CAUTION: Lacks conserved residue(s) required for the propagation of
CC       feature annotation. {ECO:0000256|HAMAP-Rule:MF_01409}.
CC   -!- CAUTION: The sequence shown here is derived from an EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ
CC       whole genome shotgun (WGS) entry which is preliminary data.
CC       {ECO:0000313|EMBL:HHR96991.1}.
